news.title: Six more months for roll-out of ‘One State, One Registration’ in Maharashtra
news.para: Initially included in govt's 100-day programme, the scheme has been partially rolled out with intra-district registration launched on May 1. However, officials said after Tuesday's meeting at Mantralaya that the complex inter-district system would require additional time.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC flags rising property fraud against NRIs in Punjab
news.para: According to the court, the gravity of such acts extends far beyond individual transactions, as they corrode institutional credibility and social conscience.

news.title: Buying or selling property? Sub-registrars in Karnataka to inform income tax department
news.para: Submitting SSFT to the income tax department is obligatory under section 285BA(1) of the Income Tax Act-1961. The trigger for the circular, sources say, is that the I-T department had raised concerns about "several" sub-registrars failing to provide these statements.

news.title: Soon, citizens in Ahmedabad can self assess future property tax
news.para: Applicants for new property valuations will be able to submit property details in the software, which will provide them with an estimate of the future property tax amount.

news.title: Rajasthan CM okays detailed project report of Jaipur metro phase-II
news.para: The project on the 42.80-km stretch from Todi Mode to Prahladpura would be implemented by Rajasthan Metro Rail Corporation, a new 50:50 joint venture company of the state and Central government.

news.title: Home loan borrowers drop 35% in FY25, but average mortgage size grows in Gujarat
news.para: However, the number of loan accounts dropped sharply by over 35%, from 6.9 lakh to just 4.46 lakh, according to data from the State Level Bankers' Committee (SLBC) – Gujarat.

news.title: No SC relief, but its nod must to bring in new developers for Jaiprakash Associates projects
news.para: YEIDA now has initiated the process of appointing a consultant for evaluating the 1,000-hectare special development zone (SDZ) land that was allotted to JAL.

news.title: Now, insolvency resolutions exceed liquidations
news.para: This improvement is partly because the legacy cases related to liquidation have come down and also due to better quality of assets when they are admitted for corporate insolvency resolution.

news.title: BMC invites developers for redevelopment of 64 slums across Mumbai
news.para: According to the public notice, the redevelopment will be carried out in line with the Development Control and Promotion Regulations (DCPR-2034) norms and applicable govt policies.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP warns RWAs of action against illegal construction in societies
news.para: The move comes after a complaint from Vipul Belmonte residents, alleging that their acting RWA president installed an illegal tin shed and leased it to a third party for a cloud kitchen without official approval, said district town planner (enforcement) Amit Madholia.

news.title: SC rejects finance ministry’s plea against input tax credits for commercial rentals
news.para: A Bench led by Justice AS Oka while dismissing the ministry’s plea on Tuesday said that it has gone through the review petition and the October 3 judgment, which has been sought to be reviewed, and “there is no error apparent on the record.”

news.title: HC seeks HSVP reply over pond land allocation for private housing in Panchkula
news.para: The land of the pond situated in Bhainsa Tibba village in MDC, which was originally acquired for public purposes by the govt, was allotted to Softobiz Technologies Private Limited for Rs 24.52 crore in June 2024 for construction of multi-crore apartments.

news.title: MHADA declares 96 extremely dangerous cessed buildings in Mumbai
news.para: Based on this year’s survey, 96 buildings have been classified as extremely dangerous. This includes two buildings that were also declared extremely dangerous in the previous year.

news.title: Nearly 100 hotels in Ghaziabad without papers to face legal action
news.para: City magistrate Santosh Upadhyay said the administration has launched a verification drive and begun issuing notices to such establishments. "We have already sent notices to 10 hotels and are in the process of sending them to the rest," he said.

news.title: PM to inaugurate Indore metro phase 1 along with Datia & Satna airports on May 31
news.para: "PM Modi will participate in the women empowerment programme and women's conference organised on May 31 on the 300th birth anniversary of Devi Ahilyabai Holkar," Kailash Vijayvargiya told reporters after a cabinet meeting.

news.title: Nearly entire Delhi-Meerut RRTS corridor set to open by June 2025
news.para: ​The 82-kilometre-long corridor, known as the Namo Bharat corridor, is being implemented by the National Capital Region Transport Corporation (NCRTC) as a high-speed regional connectivity project.

news.title: Schloss Bangalore to float ₹3,500-crore IPO on May 26
news.para: The initial share-sale will be open for public subscription during May 26-28. The one-day bidding for anchor investors will open for a day on May 23, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Ayodhya civic body's limits to widen with 343 more villages
news.para: In a significant move, the development authority has widened the scope of Ayodhya Municipal Corporation to Bhadarsa town municipality and Nawabganj Municipal Council. The expanded area will be reflected in the Ayodhya Master Plan 2031.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces' profit rises 24% to ₹19 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Total income increased to Rs 174.14 crore during January-March period of 2024-25 from Rs 120.10 crore in the year-ago period, according to a regulatory filing on Tuesday.

news.title: Safety norms go up in smoke, officials seek more teeth to Telangana fire act
news.para: The current norms are easy to bypass and penalties are so low that it does little to stop violations even when there are deaths, fire officials said.
